parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and violent shaking of the steering wheel, also known as the "death wobble," can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes violently
the vehicle wanders or pulls to one side
the steering feels loose or unstable
the vehicle is difficult to control
especially at highway speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of power steering can make the vehicle difficult to control, especially at low speeds, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power steering fails
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the vehicle is hard to maneuver
especially at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering gearbox or steering system can cause the vehicle to lose directional control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The steering gearbox fails
the steering system malfunctions
the vehicle wanders or pulls to one side
the steering feels loose or unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or even catch fire, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
burning odor
and smoke coming from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or even catch fire, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the transmission grinds or makes unusual noises
the vehicle loses power
and the backup camera is inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system malfunction can cause the vehicle to catch fire, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Smoke coming from the engine compartment
electrical wire burning
and the vehicle catching fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle and locker can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or even catch fire, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clunky noise from the rear axle
the rear locker engages unexpectedly
and the vehicle is unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sun visor can cause obstruction of the driver's view, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The sun visor falls down or breaks off
obstructing the driver's view
and can cause accidents or near-misses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the defrost system can cause visibility issues, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially during inclement weather.
symptoms: The defrost system only blows air from the center vents
causing ice and snow to build up on the windshield
obstructing the driver's view.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The spontaneous cracking of the windshield can cause visibility issues and accidents.
symptoms: The windshield cracks suddenly
without any impact or trauma
causing visibility issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the washer fluid system can cause visibility issues, especially during inclement weather.
symptoms: The washer fluid does not spray properly
causing visibility issues
especially during rain or snow.
